// Content Sprint 8: Shipping, Orders and Fulfilment.
window.CONTENT_SPRINT_8 = {"shipping-strategy":{"summary":"Choose where shipping is calculated and who manages the marketplace shipping proposition, then define how checkout charges, Marketplacer Order values, Seller responsibilities and customer expectations stay aligned.","audience":["Marketplace leadership","Marketplace operations","Seller onboarding","Ecommerce and technology","Customer experience","Finance"],"sections":{"First Decide Where Shipping Is Calculated":"<p>Before configuring shipping, decide which system will calculate the amount shown to and paid by the customer at checkout. Marketplacer Shipping Rules are one option, but they are not the only option. Depending on the marketplace architecture, shipping may be calculated by:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>Marketplacer Shipping Rules queried by the connected storefront or integration</li>\n<li>the ecommerce storefront</li>\n<li>a carrier, shipping aggregator or third-party logistics provider</li>\n<li>the Seller's connected ecommerce platform</li>\n<li>a custom shipping engine</li>\n<li>agreed Seller-level or product-level flat charges</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The checkout calculation and the Marketplacer Order record are related, but they are separate steps. The chosen checkout solution determines the shipping amount presented to the customer. When the paid Order is created in Marketplacer, the integration supplies the final postage amount for each relevant Line Item. Marketplacer records the postage amount submitted with the Order and carries it into the Seller Invoice.</p>\n<div class=\"callout note\">\n<strong>The calculation source can vary, but the transaction values must reconcile.</strong> Whether the rate came from Marketplacer Shipping Rules or another system, the postage amount sent to Marketplacer should match the amount charged at checkout.\n</div>\n<p>The Operator must confirm:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>which system owns the checkout calculation</li>\n<li>how shipping is allocated between Sellers and Line Items</li>\n<li>which postage and postage tax values are sent to Marketplacer</li>\n<li>how the storefront, payment record, Marketplacer Invoice and Seller remittance reconcile</li>\n<li>what happens when checkout succeeds but the Order is created with missing or incorrect postage</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Example: how a Shipping Profile leads to a shipping cost</h3>\n<p>A Shipping Profile does not contain a price by itself. It classifies the Variant so the connected checkout can find a matching Shipping Rule. The Rule connects the Variant's Profile and the customer's delivery Zone to one or more Shipping Rates.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Shipping Profile</th>\n<th>Shipping Zone</th>\n<th>Shipping Rate</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Big and Bulky</td>\n<td>Melbourne Metro</td>\n<td>Bulky Delivery, $69</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div>\n<ol>\n<li>A Seller assigns an oak dining table Variant to <strong>Big and Bulky</strong>.</li>\n<li>The customer enters postcode <code>3000</code>.</li>\n<li>Postcode <code>3000</code> belongs to the <strong>Melbourne Metro</strong> Zone.</li>\n<li>The matching Rule returns <strong>Bulky Delivery, $69</strong>.</li>\n<li>The connected storefront displays $69 at checkout.</li>\n<li>After payment, the integration creates the Marketplacer Order and submits <code>6900</code> cents as postage for the Line Item.</li>\n<li>Marketplacer records $69 postage on the Seller Invoice.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>If an external carrier engine calculates $74 instead, the integration submits <code>7400</code> cents and Marketplacer records $74. Shipping Rules help determine a rate before purchase. They are not reapplied after purchase to replace the postage submitted with the Order.</p>","Operator-Managed Shipping":"<p>In an Operator-managed model, the marketplace defines the shipping proposition and maintains the structures used by the connected checkout.</p>\n<p>This model is useful when the Operator wants:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>consistent delivery options and service names across Sellers</li>\n<li>central control over supported destinations and rates</li>\n<li>predictable customer-facing behaviour</li>\n<li>simpler Seller onboarding</li>\n<li>marketplace-wide rules for free shipping, bulky products or service levels</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The Operator may maintain Seller flat rates, product-level charges, Shipping Profiles, Zones, Rates and Rules depending on the solution design.</p>\n<p>Only the Operator can create Shipping Profiles. This remains true when Sellers are permitted to create their own Zones, Rates and Rules.</p>\n<div class=\"callout note\">\n<strong>Configuration alone does not change checkout.</strong> Shipping Rules are queried through the API. The storefront or integration must implement the business logic that interprets the returned Rules and Rates.\n</div>\n<p>Where Sellers should not configure their own rules, review <strong>Configuration → Seller Settings → Disable Shipping Settings</strong>, then verify the result using a test Seller account.</p>\n<h3>Operator responsibilities</h3>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>define the services the customer may see</li>\n<li>create and govern Shipping Profiles</li>\n<li>decide whether Sellers may override marketplace Rules</li>\n<li>maintain marketplace-wide Zones, Rates and Rules where used</li>\n<li>confirm how shipping is combined in a multi-Seller cart</li>\n<li>define shipping tax and commission treatment</li>\n<li>test unsupported destinations and Variants without a valid Profile</li>\n<li>monitor dispatch and tracking performance after launch</li>\n</ul>","Seller-Managed Shipping":"<p>A Seller-managed model gives Sellers more control over rates that reflect their warehouse locations, carrier agreements and product range.</p>\n<p>Depending on the configuration and integration, Sellers may maintain:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>domestic and international flat rates</li>\n<li>product-level charges</li>\n<li>Seller-defined Zones, Rates and Rules</li>\n<li>delivery services based on Seller warehouse locations</li>\n<li>fulfilment information through a connected source system</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Seller-defined Rules override the Operator-defined Rules for that Seller. Operator and Seller Rules cannot be mixed within the same Seller rule set. A Seller that overrides the marketplace Rules must define a complete compatible set of Zones, Rates and Rules using the Profiles created by the Operator.</p>\n<div class=\"callout decision\">\n<strong>Seller-managed does not mean ungoverned.</strong> The Operator should still define the allowed Profiles, service naming, supported destinations, review process and launch evidence.\n</div>\n<p>The Operator Portal does not provide one consolidated view of every Seller-created Rule and Rate. Review Seller-specific configuration through the relevant Seller Portal and include evidence in the Seller launch checklist.</p>","Mixed Model":"<p>Many marketplaces use a mixed model. Examples include:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>Operator-managed Rules for most Sellers and Seller-managed Rules for approved exceptions</li>\n<li>flat shipping for standard products and a different approach for big and bulky items</li>\n<li>Operator-created Profiles with Seller-created Zones, Rates and Rules</li>\n<li>marketplace-managed standard delivery with a third-party provider calculating specialist services</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Apply the model by a clear Seller or product segment. Avoid overlapping approaches whose outcome cannot be explained to customers, Sellers or customer service.</p>\n<p>For each launch Seller, record:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>who owns configuration</li>\n<li>which system calculates the rate</li>\n<li>which Profiles are allowed</li>\n<li>supported and excluded destinations</li>\n<li>who funds free or subsidised delivery</li>\n<li>how changes are approved and tested</li>\n</ul>","Flat Shipping":"<p>A Seller-level flat rate applies one charge to the Seller portion of a cart. In a multi-Seller cart, separate shipping charges may apply for each participating Seller.</p>\n<p>Flat shipping works well when:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>products have broadly similar fulfilment costs</li>\n<li>simplicity is more important than exact carrier cost recovery</li>\n<li>the Seller can absorb cost variation across Orders</li>\n<li>the marketplace wants predictable customer messaging</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Define whether the flat rate applies to domestic or international shipping, all products or an approved subset, and all supported destinations or only selected regions.</p>\n<p>Test:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>one item from one Seller</li>\n<li>several items from one Seller</li>\n<li>items from several Sellers</li>\n<li>a cart containing a product-level surcharge</li>\n<li>a free-shipping threshold</li>\n</ul>","Product-Level Shipping":"<p>Product-level shipping supports products that do not fit the standard Seller rate, such as furniture, appliances or oversized sporting goods.</p>\n<p>The charge may be used as:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>an incremental per-item amount</li>\n<li>an additional surcharge</li>\n<li>a specialist product rate</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"callout note\">\n<strong>Validate quantity behaviour.</strong> Where the charge is applied per item or quantity, purchasing more than one unit may multiply the shipping amount.\n</div>\n<p>Document how product-level charges interact with Seller flat rates, Shipping Rules, free-shipping offers and multi-Seller carts.</p>","Big and Bulky":"<p>Big and bulky products require an explicit model because the cost and service requirements can differ significantly from standard parcels.</p>\n<p>Define:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>the size, weight or handling criteria</li>\n<li>the dedicated Shipping Profile</li>\n<li>supported postcodes and excluded areas</li>\n<li>rate and service names</li>\n<li>appointment, kerbside, room-of-choice or installation requirements</li>\n<li>failed-delivery and return-collection responsibility</li>\n<li>carrier or fulfilment-provider ownership</li>\n<li>whether any post-order charges are permitted</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Shipping Profile</th>\n<th>Zone</th>\n<th>Example outcome</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Standard</td>\n<td>Supported domestic postcodes</td>\n<td>Standard delivery rate</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Big and Bulky</td>\n<td>Selected metropolitan postcodes</td>\n<td>Bulky delivery rate</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Big and Bulky</td>\n<td>Unsupported postcode</td>\n<td>No valid rate or approved manual process</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div>\n<p>Prefer accurate checkout pricing. Additional Charges Invoices should be reserved for a governed exception, not used as a routine substitute for an incomplete shipping design.</p>","Free Shipping":"<p>Free shipping may be configured through thresholds, promotions or another connected checkout rule.</p>\n<p>Before enabling it, decide:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>whether the threshold is marketplace-wide or per Seller</li>\n<li>whether discounts are applied before or after the threshold calculation</li>\n<li>which products, Sellers or destinations are excluded</li>\n<li>whether a big and bulky surcharge remains payable</li>\n<li>whether the Operator or Seller funds the delivery cost</li>\n<li>how the commercial outcome appears in reporting and remittance</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"callout note\">\n<strong>Free to the customer is not free to the marketplace.</strong> The Seller agreement and finance design must identify who carries the cost.\n</div>\n<p>Test below-threshold, exactly-at-threshold and above-threshold carts, including carts with multiple Sellers and excluded products.</p>","3PL Integrations":"<p>A carrier or third-party fulfilment integration may calculate delivery using product weight, dimensions, destination, service level and carrier availability.</p>\n<p>Before using a provider:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>confirm whether it calculates rates at checkout, manages fulfilment after purchase, or both</li>\n<li>define the source of truth for weight and dimensions</li>\n<li>validate multi-Seller and multi-parcel Orders</li>\n<li>confirm how carrier and tracking data return to Marketplacer and the storefront</li>\n<li>test partial fulfilment and split Shipments</li>\n<li>assign support ownership across the Operator, Seller, provider and integration partner</li>\n<li>define a fallback for provider outages or missing parcel data</li>\n</ul>","Operator Readiness Checklist":"<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>Shipping calculation owner is documented</li>\n<li>Checkout postage and Marketplacer postage reconcile</li>\n<li>Operator-managed, Seller-managed or mixed ownership is defined for every launch Seller</li>\n<li>Profiles are created and assigned to applicable Variants</li>\n<li>supported and unsupported destinations are tested</li>\n<li>flat, product-level, bulky and free-shipping behaviour is understood</li>\n<li>shipping tax and commission treatment is approved</li>\n<li>3PL ownership and fallback processes are documented</li>\n<li>customer messaging explains multi-Seller and split-delivery outcomes</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/4420678004493-About-shipping-rules\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">About shipping rules</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/11406856743693-About-shipping-rates\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">About shipping rates</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/11406928306445-Set-up-shipping-rules-operator\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Set up shipping rules as an Operator</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/seller-api/examples/shipping/howto_shippingrules/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">How to use Shipping Rules through the Seller API</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/operator-api/reference/mutations/ordercreate/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">orderCreate</a></li>\n</ul>"},"related":[["shipping-fulfilment-decisions","Shipping and Fulfilment Decisions"],["default-seller-configuration","Seller Configuration"],["product-model","Product Model"],["commission-packages","Commission Packages"],["integration-architecture","Integration Architecture"]]},"shipping-rules":{"summary":"Configure the Profiles, Zones, Rates and Rules used to determine available delivery charges, then ensure the connected checkout interprets them correctly.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Seller onboarding","Catalogue teams","Ecommerce and technology","Sellers"],"sections":{"How Shipping Rules Work":"<p>A Shipping Rule links one or more Shipping Profiles, Shipping Zones and Shipping Rates.</p>\n<p>The calculation model is:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>The purchased Variant supplies a Shipping Profile.</li>\n<li>The customer postcode identifies one or more Shipping Zones.</li>\n<li>The matching Rule links the Profile and Zone to available Rates.</li>\n<li>The connected storefront or integration applies its business logic and presents the valid customer options.</li>\n</ol>\n<pre class=\"structure-diagram\"><code>Variant Shipping Profile + Delivery Zone + Shipping Rule = Available Shipping Rate(s)</code></pre>\n<p>Create Profiles, Zones and Rates before creating the Rule.</p>\n<div class=\"callout decision\">\n<strong>Shipping Rules are pre-order data.</strong> They help a connected implementation calculate shipping once a delivery address is known. The storefront must query the Rules and decide how they apply to a Line Item or cart.\n</div>","Shipping Profiles":"<p>A Shipping Profile classifies the delivery requirements of a Variant. Typical examples include:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>Small parcel</li>\n<li>Standard</li>\n<li>Large</li>\n<li>Big and Bulky</li>\n<li>Chilled</li>\n<li>Morning Delivery</li>\n<li>Afternoon Delivery</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Only the Operator can create Shipping Profiles. Sellers can assign them to Variants and may use them in Seller-defined Rules where overrides are allowed.</p>\n<p>Use names that describe a stable fulfilment characteristic rather than a temporary carrier product. Document the objective criteria so Sellers classify products consistently.</p>\n<h3>Profile governance questions</h3>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>Is a Profile based on weight, dimensions, handling, temperature or service window?</li>\n<li>Which Profile is the default?</li>\n<li>Is a missing Profile allowed?</li>\n<li>Will Product Vetting or Catalog Rules prevent launch without one?</li>\n<li>Who approves a new Profile?</li>\n</ul>","Shipping Zones":"<p>A Shipping Zone is a named set of postal codes. Marketplacer stores the values supplied in the Zone file and returns them through the API. The connected implementation determines how wildcard or range conventions are interpreted.</p>\n<p>Zones may represent:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>metropolitan, regional and remote delivery areas</li>\n<li>Seller warehouse service areas</li>\n<li>same-day or next-day eligibility</li>\n<li>islands or restricted destinations</li>\n<li>state-based delivery groupings</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Use one clearly governed source for postcode coverage. Avoid overlapping Zones unless the checkout business logic defines how priority is resolved.</p>","Shipping Rates":"<p>A Shipping Rate associates a service name with a cost, for example:</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Rate name</th>\n<th style=\"text-align:right\">Cost</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Standard Delivery</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right\">$8</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Express Delivery</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right\">$15</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Bulky Delivery</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right\">$69</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div>\n<p>The Rate name should be understandable to the integration team and customer experience team. The connected implementation decides whether a Rate applies per Line Item, per quantity, once per Seller Invoice or once per cart.</p>\n<p>Document:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>service-level meaning</li>\n<li>cost</li>\n<li>tax treatment</li>\n<li>flat or incremental calculation</li>\n<li>delivery estimate shown to the customer</li>\n<li>who may change the Rate</li>\n</ul>","Postcodes and State-Based Rates":"<p>Postcode data should be treated as configuration that requires ownership and change control.</p>\n<p>A state-based model may use separate Zones such as:</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Zone</th>\n<th>Included postcodes</th>\n<th>Example Rate</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>NSW Metro</td>\n<td>Approved NSW metropolitan postcodes</td>\n<td>Next Day, $10</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Other States</td>\n<td>Supported postcodes outside NSW</td>\n<td>Standard, $20</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Remote</td>\n<td>Approved remote postcodes</td>\n<td>Remote Delivery, $35</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div>\n<p>Before launch:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>confirm postcode format and leading-zero handling</li>\n<li>test border postcodes and overlapping Zones</li>\n<li>define treatment for an unmatched postcode</li>\n<li>review remote and restricted areas</li>\n<li>retain the source file and approval history</li>\n</ul>","Assigning Profiles to Variants":"<p>The Shipping Profile is assigned at Variant level because different purchasable versions may have different fulfilment requirements.</p>\n<p>For example:</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Variant</th>\n<th>Shipping Profile</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>500 ml bottle</td>\n<td>Standard</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>10 litre carton</td>\n<td>Large</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>80 kg appliance</td>\n<td>Big and Bulky</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div>\n<p>Sellers can assign Profiles through supported manual, spreadsheet or API workflows. Product ingestion and Mapping do not remove the need to validate the final Variant assignment.</p>\n<div class=\"callout warning\">\n<strong>A Rule cannot return the intended Rate when the Variant has the wrong Profile.</strong> Include Profile validation in product onboarding and pre-launch testing.\n</div>","Seller Overrides":"<p>Sellers may use Operator-defined Rules or override them with Seller-defined Zones, Rates and Rules when the marketplace permits this.</p>\n<p>When a Seller overrides:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>Operator and Seller Rules cannot be mixed</li>\n<li>the Seller must recreate the relevant Zones, Rates and Rules</li>\n<li>the Seller must use Operator-created Profiles</li>\n<li>the Seller configuration must remain compatible with the Operator's checkout implementation</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Record the override decision in the Seller configuration and launch checklist. Test the Seller's own delivery origin, service areas and unavailable destinations.</p>","Testing Shipping Rules":"<p>Test the Rule through the actual connected checkout or API implementation, not only by reviewing the Operator Portal.</p>\n<p>Include:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>one valid standard postcode</li>\n<li>one regional or remote postcode</li>\n<li>one unsupported postcode</li>\n<li>one Variant without a Profile</li>\n<li>one Variant with the wrong Profile</li>\n<li>two available Rates for the same Profile and Zone</li>\n<li>a multi-Seller cart</li>\n<li>a Seller override</li>\n<li>quantity changes</li>\n<li>free or zero-cost delivery where intended</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Confirm that the amount displayed at checkout is the amount sent to Marketplacer when the Order is created.</p>","Operator Readiness Checklist":"<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>Profile definitions and owners are documented</li>\n<li>Zone files are approved and version-controlled</li>\n<li>Rate names, costs and tax treatment are approved</li>\n<li>every Rule has the intended Profile, Zone and Rate relationship</li>\n<li>applicable Variants have the correct Profile</li>\n<li>Seller overrides have been reviewed and tested</li>\n<li>unmatched postcodes produce a safe customer outcome</li>\n<li>checkout and Marketplacer postage values reconcile</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/4420678004493-About-shipping-rules\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">About shipping rules</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/11407043703053-Set-up-shipping-profiles-operator\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Set up shipping profiles as an Operator</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/11407014126989-Set-up-shipping-zones-operator\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Set up shipping zones as an Operator</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/11407115009933-Set-up-shipping-rates-operator\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Set up shipping rates as an Operator</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/11406928306445-Set-up-shipping-rules-operator\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Set up shipping rules as an Operator</a></li>\n</ul>"},"related":[["shipping-strategy","Shipping Strategy"],["product-model","Product Model"],["bulk-product-management","Bulk Product Management"],["default-seller-configuration","Seller Configuration"],["test-orders","Test the Order and Fulfilment Flow"]]},"shipping-carriers":{"summary":"Maintain the approved Carrier list and tracking-link configuration used when Sellers dispatch Orders, then validate how Shipment data reaches the customer-facing experience.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Seller onboarding","Customer service","Ecommerce and technology","Sellers"],"sections":{"Configure Shipment Carriers":"<p>In the Operator Portal, go to:</p>\n<p><strong>Configuration → Shipment Carriers</strong></p>\n<p>For each Carrier, configure:</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Field</th>\n<th>Purpose</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Name</td>\n<td>The Carrier shown to Sellers during dispatch</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Tracking URL</td>\n<td>The pattern used to generate a tracking link</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Carrier Homepage URL</td>\n<td>A fallback when a tracking link cannot be generated</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Alternative Carrier Names</td>\n<td>Other names a Seller system may submit for the same Carrier</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div>\n<p>Carrier names and alternative names must be unique. Use a recognisable business name and maintain one approved record for each Carrier.</p>","Tracking URL Pattern":"<p>The Tracking URL should contain the placeholder:</p>\n<pre class=\"structure-diagram\"><code>{TRACKING_NUMBER}</code></pre>\n<p>Example:</p>\n<pre class=\"structure-diagram\"><code>https://carrier.example/track/{TRACKING_NUMBER}</code></pre>\n<p>When the Seller dispatches with tracking number <code>ABC123456</code>, the generated URL becomes:</p>\n<pre class=\"structure-diagram\"><code>https://carrier.example/track/ABC123456</code></pre>\n<p>The Tracking URL is optional when the Carrier is configured, but it is required for Marketplacer to generate a Carrier-specific link in Marketplacer-generated dispatch communication. The Carrier Homepage URL is used as a fallback where applicable.</p>\n<div class=\"callout note\">\n<strong>A tracking number alone does not guarantee a working customer link.</strong> The Carrier must be recognised and correctly configured, or the Seller API must provide a tracking URL directly.\n</div>","Alternative Carrier Names":"<p>Seller systems may use different names for the same Carrier.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Approved Carrier</th>\n<th>Possible submitted names</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Australia Post</td>\n<td>AusPost, Aus Post, AustraliaPost</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div>\n<p>Rather than creating duplicate Carrier records, add the submitted names as alternatives.</p>\n<p>If an unrecognised Carrier name is submitted, the Shipment can still be created, but Marketplacer will not generate the configured Carrier homepage or tracking URL.</p>","How Sellers Provide Dispatch Information":"<p>When dispatching through the Seller Portal, the Seller supplies:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>quantity being dispatched</li>\n<li>tracking number</li>\n<li>Carrier</li>\n<li>optional Shipment note</li>\n<li>fulfil-from address where configured</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The Seller can dispatch the entire Invoice or only selected Line Items or quantities. Marketplacer creates one or more Shipments against the Seller Invoice.</p>\n<p>Sellers connected through an ecommerce or order-management platform should normally dispatch from that connected system, not repeat the same dispatch in the Seller Portal.</p>","Customer Tracking Experience":"<p>Marketplacer stores the Shipment, Carrier, tracking number, dispatch date and shipped quantities. A connected storefront can retrieve this data and decide how tracking is displayed to the customer.</p>\n<p>Validate the complete journey:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Seller dispatches the item.</li>\n<li>Marketplacer creates the Shipment.</li>\n<li>The storefront receives the update.</li>\n<li>The customer sees the correct Carrier and tracking number.</li>\n<li>The tracking link opens the intended Carrier page.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Document which system sends the dispatch email and how multiple tracking numbers appear for partial or split Shipments.</p>","What to Test":"<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>complete dispatch with one tracking number</li>\n<li>partial dispatch</li>\n<li>multiple Shipments against one Seller Invoice</li>\n<li>multiple Sellers within one customer Order</li>\n<li>alternative Carrier names</li>\n<li>unrecognised Carrier name</li>\n<li>missing tracking number</li>\n<li>edited tracking information after dispatch</li>\n<li>fulfil-from address where used</li>\n<li>tracking displayed in the storefront and customer communication</li>\n</ul>","Operator Readiness Checklist":"<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>approved Carriers are configured in both environments</li>\n<li>Tracking URLs contain the correct placeholder</li>\n<li>Carrier Homepage URLs are valid</li>\n<li>known alternative names are configured</li>\n<li>Seller onboarding explains the approved Carrier names</li>\n<li>the storefront displays partial and multiple Shipments correctly</li>\n<li>customer service can locate and explain tracking information</li>\n<li>correction and resynchronisation behaviour has been tested</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/4416029335309-Manage-shipping-carriers\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Manage shipping carriers</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/8838299197197-Dispatch-orders-from-the-Seller-Portal\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Dispatch orders from the Seller Portal</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/8838609979533-Edit-shipping-details-after-dispatch\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Edit shipping details after dispatch</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/seller-api/examples/shipping/creating_shipments/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Creating Shipments</a></li>\n</ul>"},"related":[["shipping-rules","Shipping Rules"],["fulfilment","Fulfilment and Dispatch"],["order-exceptions","Order Exceptions"],["default-seller-configuration","Seller Configuration"],["test-orders","Test the Order and Fulfilment Flow"]]},"order-architecture":{"summary":"Understand how one customer checkout becomes a Marketplacer Order, how it is separated into Seller Invoices and how purchased Variants become the Line Items Sellers fulfil.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Customer service","Finance","Seller onboarding","Ecommerce and technology","Sellers"],"sections":{"One Customer Checkout, Several Operational Records":"<p>A customer may complete one checkout containing products from one or several Sellers.</p>\n<pre class=\"structure-diagram\"><code>Customer checkout\n└── Marketplacer Order\n    ├── Seller 1 Invoice\n    │   ├── Line Item A\n    │   └── Line Item B\n    └── Seller 2 Invoice\n        └── Line Item C</code></pre>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>The <strong>Order</strong> represents the complete marketplace purchase.</li>\n<li>An <strong>Invoice</strong> represents one Seller's portion of the Order.</li>\n<li>A <strong>Line Item</strong> represents a purchased Variant and quantity.</li>\n<li>A <strong>Shipment</strong> records full or partial dispatch against an Invoice.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Even when only one Seller participates, Marketplacer creates an Invoice for that Seller.</p>","Customer Checkout and Payment":"<p>In a connected marketplace, the customer normally browses, checks out and pays through the Operator's ecommerce storefront.</p>\n<p>The storefront commonly manages:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>the customer account and cart</li>\n<li>delivery and billing addresses</li>\n<li>customer-facing delivery methods</li>\n<li>payment authorisation and capture</li>\n<li>promotions presented at checkout</li>\n<li>first-party products</li>\n<li>customer Order confirmation and account pages</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The integration then creates the marketplace Order in Marketplacer at the agreed payment event.</p>\n<div class=\"callout warning\">\n<strong>Define the payment-to-order sequence.</strong> The integration must handle payment succeeding while Marketplacer Order creation fails, and it must prevent duplicate Orders during retries.\n</div>","Creating the Marketplacer Order":"<p>Connected implementations normally use the Operator GraphQL API <code>orderCreate</code> mutation.</p>\n<p>The request may include:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>customer and delivery details</li>\n<li>Marketplacer Variant IDs</li>\n<li>quantities</li>\n<li>item cost and tax</li>\n<li>postage and postage tax</li>\n<li>promotions and adjustments</li>\n<li>storefront Order references</li>\n<li>external IDs and metadata</li>\n<li>Seller notification instructions where used</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The most common approach supplies Line Items and lets Marketplacer group them into Seller Invoices automatically. An integration can instead supply Invoice-level inputs, but then it is responsible for creating the correct Invoice for each Seller.</p>\n<h3>Order creation controls</h3>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>use a stable storefront external ID</li>\n<li>make retry handling idempotent</li>\n<li>preserve the completed checkout values</li>\n<li>log requests, responses and returned IDs</li>\n<li>alert when Order creation fails</li>\n<li>prevent a manual replacement Order from duplicating an existing transaction</li>\n</ul>","Multi-Seller Order Splitting":"<p>Example:</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Purchased item</th>\n<th>Supplied by</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Coffee machine</td>\n<td>Seller A</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Coffee pods</td>\n<td>Seller A</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Toaster</td>\n<td>Seller B</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div>\n<p>Marketplacer creates:</p>\n<pre class=\"structure-diagram\"><code>Order 10045\n├── Invoice for Seller A\n│   ├── Coffee machine\n│   └── Coffee pods\n└── Invoice for Seller B\n    └── Toaster</code></pre>\n<p>Each Seller fulfils independently. One customer Order may therefore have different dispatch dates, Carriers, tracking numbers, return outcomes and remittance timings.</p>\n<p>The customer-facing experience should explain that items from different Sellers may arrive separately.</p>","Seller Invoices":"<p>An Invoice is the Seller's operational view of the Order. It supports:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>Seller notification</li>\n<li>fulfilment and tracking</li>\n<li>cancellations and returns</li>\n<li>Invoice Amendments</li>\n<li>commission calculations</li>\n<li>remittance and payout processing</li>\n</ul>\n<p>A Seller manages the Invoice through the Seller Portal, MConnect, the Seller GraphQL API or another approved integration.</p>\n<p>The Seller API is Invoice-centred because the Seller should only access the part of the purchase that belongs to that Seller.</p>","Line Items":"<p>A Line Item is created when a Marketplacer Variant is purchased. It contains the purchased quantity and transaction-specific financial values.</p>\n<p>Operational actions can apply at Line Item or quantity level:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>only one Line Item may be dispatched</li>\n<li>part of a quantity may be dispatched</li>\n<li>one Line Item may be cancelled while another is fulfilled</li>\n<li>postage, tax or promotion values may differ</li>\n<li>a return may apply to only part of the Invoice</li>\n</ul>","Products, Adverts and Variants":"<p>Marketplacer uses specific product terminology:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>a <strong>Product</strong> is called an <strong>Advert</strong> in many platform and API areas</li>\n<li>an Advert contains one or more <strong>Variants</strong></li>\n<li>the customer purchases a Variant</li>\n<li>the purchased Variant becomes a Line Item</li>\n</ul>\n<pre class=\"structure-diagram\"><code>Advert: Classic Cotton T-shirt\n├── Variant: Black / Medium\n├── Variant: Black / Large\n└── Variant: White / Medium</code></pre>\n<p>When the customer purchases Black / Medium, that Variant becomes the Line Item on the Seller Invoice.</p>","First-Party and Marketplace Products":"<p>A connected storefront may contain first-party Operator products and third-party Seller products.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Customer item</th>\n<th>Supply model</th>\n<th>Typical Marketplacer result</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Item A</td>\n<td>Seller A</td>\n<td>Included in Seller A Invoice</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Item B</td>\n<td>Operator first-party stock</td>\n<td>Remains in the storefront system</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Item C</td>\n<td>Seller B</td>\n<td>Included in Seller B Invoice</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div>\n<p>The Operator should define how customer service sees the complete purchase, how fulfilment statuses are combined and how cancellations and refunds are routed for each supply model.</p>","Identifiers and Reconciliation":"<p>Preserve and make searchable:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>storefront Order ID</li>\n<li>Marketplacer Order ID</li>\n<li>Seller Invoice ID</li>\n<li>Line Item ID</li>\n<li>Shipment ID</li>\n<li>payment transaction reference</li>\n<li>cancellation or refund reference</li>\n<li>Seller source-system Order ID where applicable</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"callout decision\">\n<strong>Always confirm which identifier is being discussed.</strong> A Marketplacer Order and Seller Invoice are related records, but they are not interchangeable.\n</div>","Historical Transaction Values":"<p>Use the values stored on the Order, Invoice and Line Items when investigating a completed transaction.</p>\n<p>Do not reconstruct a historical Order from current product data. The title, price, tax, Profile, SKU or availability may have changed after purchase.</p>","Operator Readiness Checklist":"<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>one correct Marketplacer Order is created for each eligible checkout</li>\n<li>one Invoice is created for each participating Seller</li>\n<li>first-party items remain in the intended system</li>\n<li>Variant IDs, quantities and financial values are correct</li>\n<li>stable external IDs connect the systems</li>\n<li>duplicate creation is prevented</li>\n<li>failed Order creation is monitored</li>\n<li>Sellers only receive their own Invoice information</li>\n<li>customer service can locate the complete customer journey</li>\n<li>split fulfilment is explained to customers</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/operator-api/examples/orders/howto_order/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Creating Orders</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/operator-api/reference/mutations/ordercreate/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">orderCreate</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/seller-api/examples/orders/invoices/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">How to query Orders</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/seller-api/examples/shipping/creating_shipments/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Creating Shipments</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/28414815410445-Shopify-Plus-How-data-is-synchronized\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Shopify Plus: How data is synchronized</a></li>\n</ul>"},"related":[["marketplace-terminology","Marketplace Terminology"],["end-to-end-flow","End-to-End Marketplace Flow"],["integration-architecture","Integration Architecture"],["order-lifecycle","Order Lifecycle"],["refund-foundations","Refund Foundations"]]},"order-lifecycle":{"summary":"Follow a marketplace transaction from customer checkout through Seller fulfilment, Shipment tracking and remittance, and understand where the lifecycle can branch into an exception.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Sellers","Customer service","Finance","Seller management","Ecommerce and technology"],"sections":{"Order Lifecycle at a Glance":"<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>Customer places and pays for the Order</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>Connected storefront creates the Marketplacer Order</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><div><strong>Marketplacer creates one Invoice per Seller</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><div><strong>Each Seller receives and processes its Invoice</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><div><strong>Seller dispatches all or part of the Line Items</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">6</span><div><strong>Marketplacer records Shipments and tracking</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">7</span><div><strong>Updates return to the connected storefront</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">8</span><div><strong>All quantities are dispatched or otherwise resolved</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">9</span><div><strong>Invoice progresses through remittance and payout processes</strong></div></div></div>\n<p>A multi-Seller Order can be partly fulfilled overall even when one Seller has completed its Invoice.</p>","Stage 1: Customer Checkout and Payment":"<p>The storefront normally owns the basket, address, customer-facing delivery options, promotions and payment processing.</p>\n<p>Define the payment event that permits the Marketplacer Order to be created, for example successful authorisation or capture. Document the response when payment succeeds but Order creation does not.</p>","Stage 2: Order Created in Marketplacer":"<p>The integration supplies purchased Variants, quantities and transaction values through <code>orderCreate</code>.</p>\n<p>Confirm:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>the correct Variant IDs are used</li>\n<li>quantities match checkout</li>\n<li>item, tax and postage values reconcile</li>\n<li>a stable external Order reference is supplied</li>\n<li>retries do not create duplicates</li>\n<li>errors are logged and surfaced</li>\n</ul>","Stage 3: Seller Invoices Created":"<p>Marketplacer separates the Order by Seller. Each Seller receives only its own Line Items and can fulfil independently.</p>\n<p>This enables different dispatch dates, Carriers, tracking numbers, cancellations, returns and remittance outcomes within one customer purchase.</p>","Stage 4: Seller Receives and Processes the Invoice":"<p>The Seller receives the Invoice through the agreed method:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>Seller Portal</li>\n<li>MConnect and the Seller's source platform</li>\n<li>Seller GraphQL API</li>\n<li>another approved order-management integration</li>\n</ul>\n<p>During onboarding, define how often the Seller checks for Orders, who owns fulfilment, the dispatch timeframe, tracking requirements and the escalation process for stock problems.</p>\n<p>A connected Seller should normally fulfil from its connected platform rather than duplicate the action in the Seller Portal.</p>","Stage 5: Seller Dispatches the Items":"<p>The Seller may dispatch:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>the entire Invoice in one Shipment</li>\n<li>selected Line Items</li>\n<li>part of a Line Item quantity</li>\n<li>remaining quantities in later Shipments</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Example:</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Line Item</th>\n<th style=\"text-align:right\">Ordered</th>\n<th style=\"text-align:right\">First Shipment</th>\n<th style=\"text-align:right\">Remaining</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Coffee mugs</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right\">3</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right\">2</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right\">1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Coffee beans</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right\">1</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right\">1</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right\">0</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div>\n<p>The first Shipment contains two mugs and the coffee beans. The remaining mug is dispatched later or resolved through cancellation.</p>","Invoice Fulfilment Status":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Fulfilment progress</th>\n<th>Seller Portal label</th>\n<th>API status flags</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Nothing dispatched</td>\n<td><strong>Paid</strong></td>\n<td><code>PAID</code></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Some, but not all, Line Items or quantities dispatched</td>\n<td><strong>Paid Partially Sent</strong></td>\n<td><code>PAID</code>, <code>PARTIALLY_SENT</code></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>All Line Items and quantities dispatched</td>\n<td><strong>Paid Sent</strong></td>\n<td><code>PAID</code>, <code>SENT</code></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div>\n<div class=\"callout note\">\n<strong>Paid does not mean the Seller has received its payout.</strong> In this context it describes the paid Order and fulfilment state in Marketplacer.\n</div>","Stage 6: Shipment and Tracking Updates":"<p>Each dispatch creates a Shipment associated with the Invoice, Line Items, quantities, Carrier, tracking number and dispatch date.</p>\n<p>The connected storefront may receive the update through a connector, API query or webhook. Confirm:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>the fulfilment source of truth</li>\n<li>expected synchronisation timing</li>\n<li>partial fulfilment mapping</li>\n<li>multiple tracking-number presentation</li>\n<li>retry and fallback behaviour</li>\n<li>whether post-dispatch edits resynchronise</li>\n</ul>","Stage 7: Invoice Completion":"<p>An Invoice should not be treated as operationally complete while unresolved quantities remain.</p>\n<p>Every quantity must be:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>dispatched, or</li>\n<li>resolved through the correct cancellation or refund workflow</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Incomplete quantities affect customer communication, dispatch SLA performance, Seller metrics, remittance and reconciliation.</p>","Stage 8: Remittance":"<p>Fulfilment contributes to remittance creation and eligibility, but it does not automatically mean the Seller has been paid.</p>\n<p>The financial workflow may also depend on:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>no outstanding Line Items</li>\n<li>the configured remittance delay</li>\n<li>manual or automatic approval</li>\n<li>refunds, cancellations, fees and adjustments</li>\n<li>the Operator's payout provider or finance process</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"callout warning\">\n<strong>Paid Sent is a fulfilment outcome, not proof that Seller funds have moved.</strong>\n</div>","Lifecycle Exceptions":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Scenario</th>\n<th>Required response</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Order creation fails</td>\n<td>Investigate and safely retry without duplication</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Seller cannot fulfil</td>\n<td>Use the pre-dispatch cancellation workflow</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Some items are available</td>\n<td>Dispatch available quantities and resolve the remainder</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Tracking does not reach storefront</td>\n<td>Investigate Shipment, Carrier and integration flow</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Customer returns an item</td>\n<td>Use the post-dispatch return workflow</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Valid post-order charge is required</td>\n<td>Follow the Additional Charges Invoice policy</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div>","Operational Ownership":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Stage</th>\n<th>Typical owner</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Checkout and payment</td>\n<td>Operator ecommerce and payment teams</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Marketplacer Order creation</td>\n<td>Integration or engineering team</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Seller Invoice receipt</td>\n<td>Seller operations</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Picking, packing and dispatch</td>\n<td>Seller</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Tracking synchronisation</td>\n<td>Seller system, connector or integration</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Customer communication</td>\n<td>Operator storefront or customer service</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Exception management</td>\n<td>Operator and Seller according to the issue</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Remittance approval</td>\n<td>Operator finance or automated workflow</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Seller payout</td>\n<td>Operator or payout provider</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div>","Operator Monitoring":"<p>Monitor:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>Orders that failed to create</li>\n<li>duplicate or mismatched Orders</li>\n<li>Invoices remaining <strong>Paid</strong></li>\n<li>Invoices remaining <strong>Paid Partially Sent</strong></li>\n<li>dispatch SLA breaches</li>\n<li>Shipments without tracking</li>\n<li>storefront and Marketplacer status mismatches</li>\n<li>remittance items awaiting action</li>\n<li>customer contacts relating to split delivery</li>\n</ul>","Operator Readiness Checklist":"<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>payment-to-order sequence is documented</li>\n<li>Seller Invoice splitting has been tested</li>\n<li>each Seller receives Orders through the intended channel</li>\n<li>complete and partial dispatch work correctly</li>\n<li>Seller Portal and storefront statuses are mapped</li>\n<li>tracking reaches the customer experience</li>\n<li>unresolved quantities follow cancellation or return processes</li>\n<li>dispatch SLA monitoring is configured</li>\n<li>fulfilment feeds the intended remittance process</li>\n<li>failed events create actionable alerts</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/operator-api/examples/orders/howto_order/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Creating Orders</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/seller-api/examples/orders/invoices/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">How to query Orders</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/8838299197197-Dispatch-orders-from-the-Seller-Portal\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Dispatch orders from the Seller Portal</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/seller-api/examples/orders/howto_invoicestatusflags/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">How to use Invoice Status Flags</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360052908272-Seller-payments-and-remittance-workflow\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Seller payments and remittance workflow</a></li>\n</ul>"},"related":[["order-architecture","Order Architecture"],["fulfilment","Fulfilment and Dispatch"],["order-exceptions","Order Exceptions"],["remittances","Remittance Configuration"],["refund-foundations","Refund Foundations"]]},"fulfilment":{"summary":"Define where each Seller fulfils Orders, how complete and partial Shipments are recorded, how tracking is supplied and how outstanding quantities are resolved.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Sellers","Seller onboarding","Customer service","Ecommerce and technology"],"sections":{"Decide Where Sellers Will Fulfil Orders":"<p>Sellers may fulfil through:</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Fulfilment method</th>\n<th>Typical use</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Connected ecommerce or order-management platform</td>\n<td>MConnect or another integration</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Marketplacer Seller Portal</td>\n<td>Manual Seller operations</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Bulk Dispatch spreadsheet</td>\n<td>High-volume manual dispatch</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Seller GraphQL API</td>\n<td>Custom order-management integration</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div>\n<div class=\"callout decision\">\n<strong>Set one fulfilment source of truth per Seller.</strong> A Seller should not dispatch the same Invoice in both its connected platform and the Seller Portal.\n</div>\n<p>Record where the Seller receives Orders, where dispatch is actioned, how tracking is supplied, whether partial fulfilment is supported and how errors are escalated.</p>","What a Seller Fulfils":"<p>The Seller fulfils the Line Items and quantities on its Invoice.</p>\n<p>The Seller may dispatch all items in one Shipment, selected Line Items, part of a quantity, or remaining items in later Shipments.</p>\n<p>Example:</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Line Item</th>\n<th style=\"text-align:right\">Quantity ordered</th>\n<th style=\"text-align:right\">First Shipment</th>\n<th style=\"text-align:right\">Remaining</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Dinner plate set</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right\">2</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right\">1</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right\">1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Serving bowl</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right\">1</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right\">1</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right\">0</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div>\n<p>After the first Shipment, the Invoice is <strong>Paid Partially Sent</strong>. It becomes <strong>Paid Sent</strong> only after the final quantity is dispatched or otherwise resolved.</p>","Dispatching an Individual Order in the Seller Portal":"<p>Seller Portal Orders should only be dispatched when they have a Paid status.</p>\n<p>The Seller goes to <strong>Orders → Outstanding</strong>, then:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Opens the Order.</li>\n<li>Enters the quantity being dispatched for each item.</li>\n<li>Enters <code>0</code> for any item excluded from this Shipment.</li>\n<li>Enters the tracking number.</li>\n<li>Selects the Carrier.</li>\n<li>Adds an optional note.</li>\n<li>Selects <strong>Dispatch</strong>.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>A complete dispatch results in <strong>Paid Sent</strong>. A partial dispatch results in <strong>Paid Partially Sent</strong>.</p>","Dispatching Orders in Bulk":"<p>Sellers with many outstanding items can use <strong>Orders → Bulk Dispatch</strong>.</p>\n<p>The Seller downloads the CSV, adds dispatch information and uploads the file again.</p>\n<p>The file may include quantity, dispatch date, tracking number, Carrier and Shipment note.</p>\n<p>Important differences from individual dispatch:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>remove a row for an item not being dispatched</li>\n<li>do not enter <code>0</code> in the bulk file</li>\n<li>Carrier names must match a configured Carrier or alternative name</li>\n<li>review processing results and correct failed rows</li>\n</ul>","Tracking Requirements":"<p>Operators should decide whether tracking is:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>mandatory for every Seller</li>\n<li>mandatory only for Sellers using Bulk Dispatch</li>\n<li>optional for delivery methods that do not provide tracking</li>\n<li>required by the Seller agreement or SLA</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Tracking expectations should be reflected in Seller onboarding, Carrier configuration, customer communication and performance monitoring.</p>","Multiple Shipments":"<p>One Seller Invoice may contain several Shipments because:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>products are stored in different locations</li>\n<li>some items are ready earlier</li>\n<li>separate Carriers are used</li>\n<li>a Line Item quantity is split</li>\n<li>large and small items ship separately</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Each Shipment can have its own Carrier and tracking number. The storefront should display every Shipment and remaining quantity correctly.</p>","Fulfil-From Addresses":"<p>Sellers with several warehouses or stores may use Shipment Addresses and select the relevant <strong>Fulfil from</strong> address during dispatch.</p>\n<p>Confirm whether the address is needed for:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>logistics integrations</li>\n<li>customer service</li>\n<li>returns routing</li>\n<li>delivery estimates</li>\n<li>Seller reporting</li>\n<li>tax or regulatory requirements</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Not every connected storefront automatically receives or displays the shipped-from address. Test the implemented integration.</p>","Invoice Status After Dispatch":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Fulfilment state</th>\n<th>Seller Portal label</th>\n<th>API status flags</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>No items dispatched</td>\n<td><strong>Paid</strong></td>\n<td><code>PAID</code></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Some Line Items or quantities dispatched</td>\n<td><strong>Paid Partially Sent</strong></td>\n<td><code>PAID</code>, <code>PARTIALLY_SENT</code></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>All Line Items and quantities dispatched</td>\n<td><strong>Paid Sent</strong></td>\n<td><code>PAID</code>, <code>SENT</code></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div>\n<div class=\"callout note\">\n<strong>Paid Sent confirms fulfilment, not Seller payout.</strong>\n</div>","Editing Shipping Details After Dispatch":"<p>A Seller can correct Carrier, tracking number, dispatch date, note and fulfil-from information after dispatch.</p>\n<p>In the Seller Portal, use <strong>Orders → Order History → Edit shipping info</strong>.</p>\n<p>An Order cannot simply be un-dispatched after the Shipment exists. The connected storefront's response to an edited Shipment depends on the integration and must be tested.</p>","Unavailable Items Must Be Resolved":"<p>A Seller should not leave an Invoice indefinitely in <strong>Paid</strong> or <strong>Paid Partially Sent</strong> because stock is unavailable.</p>\n<pre class=\"structure-diagram\"><code>Quantity ordered: 3\nQuantity dispatched: 2\nQuantity unavailable: 1</code></pre>\n<p>The final unit should not be marked as dispatched. Use the approved pre-dispatch cancellation workflow so the customer, Invoice, remittance and Seller-performance records reflect the real outcome.</p>","Dispatch SLAs":"<p>Operators can configure the expected dispatch timeframe. A partial Shipment does not complete the obligation while quantities remain outstanding.</p>\n<p>Define:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>standard and Seller-specific dispatch SLAs</li>\n<li>when a Seller must report a delay</li>\n<li>customer delay communication</li>\n<li>escalation after a breach</li>\n<li>consequences for repeat breaches</li>\n</ul>","Operator Monitoring":"<p>Review:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>Invoices remaining <strong>Paid</strong></li>\n<li>Invoices remaining <strong>Paid Partially Sent</strong></li>\n<li>approaching or breached dispatch SLAs</li>\n<li>Shipments without tracking</li>\n<li>Bulk Dispatch failures</li>\n<li>unrecognised Carrier names</li>\n<li>fulfilment updates missing from the storefront</li>\n<li>duplicate or conflicting Shipment updates</li>\n<li>Seller stock shortages</li>\n</ul>","Marketplace Decisions":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Decision</th>\n<th>Question</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Fulfilment system</td>\n<td>Where will each Seller action dispatch?</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Partial fulfilment</td>\n<td>Can an Invoice be split into several Shipments?</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Tracking</td>\n<td>When is tracking mandatory?</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Carriers</td>\n<td>Which names and alternatives are approved?</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Fulfil-from addresses</td>\n<td>Must the dispatch location be recorded?</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Customer communication</td>\n<td>Which system sends Shipment updates?</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Dispatch SLA</td>\n<td>How quickly must all quantities be resolved?</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Unavailable stock</td>\n<td>Who cancels and who informs the customer?</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Corrections</td>\n<td>How are tracking corrections resynchronised?</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Monitoring</td>\n<td>Who follows up outstanding Invoices?</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div>","End-to-End Testing":"<p>Test:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>complete dispatch</li>\n<li>partial dispatch</li>\n<li>part of a multi-quantity Line Item</li>\n<li>second Shipment for remaining quantities</li>\n<li>two Sellers dispatching the same customer Order</li>\n<li>separate Carriers and tracking numbers</li>\n<li>successful and failed Bulk Dispatch</li>\n<li>missing mandatory tracking</li>\n<li>alternative Carrier name</li>\n<li>fulfil-from address</li>\n<li>corrected tracking after dispatch</li>\n<li>unavailable quantity cancelled rather than falsely shipped</li>\n</ul>","Operator Readiness Checklist":"<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>every Seller has an agreed fulfilment method</li>\n<li>connected Sellers know where to dispatch</li>\n<li>complete and partial dispatch are tested</li>\n<li>approved Carriers are configured</li>\n<li>tracking requirements are documented</li>\n<li>fulfil-from addresses are configured where needed</li>\n<li>Shipment updates reach the storefront</li>\n<li>corrections can be processed safely</li>\n<li>unavailable stock follows cancellation</li>\n<li>dispatch SLAs are understood</li>\n<li>the Operator monitors <strong>Paid</strong> and <strong>Paid Partially Sent</strong> Invoices</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/8838299197197-Dispatch-orders-from-the-Seller-Portal\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Dispatch orders from the Seller Portal</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/4408312306061-Bulk-dispatch-orders-via-CSV-spreadsheet\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Bulk dispatch orders via CSV</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/seller-api/examples/shipping/creating_shipments/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Creating Shipments</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/seller-api/examples/orders/howto_invoicestatusflags/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">How to use Invoice Status Flags</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/8838609979533-Edit-shipping-details-after-dispatch\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Edit shipping details after dispatch</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/9091850460301-Use-multiple-shipping-addresses-as-a-seller\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Use multiple shipping addresses as a Seller</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/25570962112397-Marketplace-metrics\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Marketplace metrics</a></li>\n</ul>"},"related":[["shipping-carriers","Shipping Carriers and Tracking"],["order-lifecycle","Order Lifecycle"],["order-exceptions","Order Exceptions"],["seller-performance","Seller Performance and SLAs"],["cancellation-workflow","Cancellation Workflow"]]},"order-exceptions":{"summary":"Detect, investigate and resolve Orders that do not follow the expected path across checkout, Marketplacer, Seller systems, fulfilment, payment and customer communication.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Customer service","Finance","Seller management","Technology and integrations"],"sections":{"Use a Consistent Exception Process":"<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>Detect</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>Confirm customer, Order, Invoice, Line Item and Seller</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><div><strong>Compare all relevant systems</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><div><strong>Contain customer and financial impact</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><div><strong>Resolve through the correct workflow</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">6</span><div><strong>Reconcile all records</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">7</span><div><strong>Document cause and preventive action</strong></div></div></div>\n<div class=\"callout warning\">\n<strong>An exception is not resolved until the operational record, customer outcome and financial outcome agree.</strong>\n</div>\n<p>Avoid isolated corrections in one system without checking the storefront, Marketplacer, Seller system, payment provider, customer communication and remittance impact.</p>","Identify the Correct Transaction":"<p>Collect:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>storefront Order number</li>\n<li>Marketplacer Order ID</li>\n<li>Seller Invoice ID</li>\n<li>Line Item ID</li>\n<li>Shipment ID</li>\n<li>Seller source-system Order ID</li>\n<li>payment reference</li>\n<li>cancellation or refund reference</li>\n</ul>\n<p>External IDs allow Operators and Sellers to search for the connected transaction. Always confirm which identifier the customer, Seller or technical team is using.</p>","Common Order Exceptions":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Exception</th>\n<th>Likely impact</th>\n<th>First action</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Checkout succeeded but no Marketplacer Order exists</td>\n<td>Seller does not receive the Order</td>\n<td>Review the Order creation request and response</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Insufficient stock rejects Order creation</td>\n<td>Seller item is not routed</td>\n<td>Confirm payment and inventory state</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Duplicate Order attempt</td>\n<td>Duplicate fulfilment risk</td>\n<td>Search by external ID before retrying</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Financial values do not match</td>\n<td>Incorrect Invoice or remittance</td>\n<td>Compare item, tax, postage and adjustments</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Seller did not receive the Invoice</td>\n<td>Dispatch delay</td>\n<td>Confirm the Invoice exists and inspect the connection</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Seller cannot fulfil</td>\n<td>Customer cancellation required</td>\n<td>Stop fulfilment of that quantity and begin cancellation</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Invoice remains Paid</td>\n<td>Nothing dispatched</td>\n<td>Review Seller receipt and SLA</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Invoice remains Paid Partially Sent</td>\n<td>Quantities remain unresolved</td>\n<td>Confirm dispatch or cancellation plan</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Shipment has no working tracking</td>\n<td>Poor customer visibility</td>\n<td>Review Carrier and tracking data</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Storefront and Marketplacer statuses differ</td>\n<td>Incorrect customer experience</td>\n<td>Inspect connector or webhook processing</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div>","Order Creation Failures":"<p><code>orderCreate</code> can reject a request when required data is missing or invalid, including Variant ID, quantity, cost, address information, tax consistency, stock availability or a unique external ID.</p>\n<p>Example:</p>\n<pre class=\"structure-diagram\"><code>Storefront quantity: 2\nMarketplacer countOnHand: 1\nResult: orderCreate fails</code></pre>\n<p>Determine:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Was payment authorised or captured?</li>\n<li>Did any Marketplacer Order or Invoice create?</li>\n<li>Are other Sellers or first-party items involved?</li>\n<li>Can the item still be supplied?</li>\n<li>Is cancellation and refund required?</li>\n<li>Does inventory synchronisation need correction?</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Store the request, safe diagnostic payload, response, returned IDs, errors, retry history and final resolution.</p>","Duplicate Order Prevention":"<p>Use a stable unique external Order ID. Before retrying after a timeout:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Search for the Order using the external ID.</li>\n<li>Confirm whether the first request succeeded.</li>\n<li>Check whether Seller Invoices already exist.</li>\n<li>Retry only when the transaction is confirmed absent.</li>\n<li>Reuse the same stable reference.</li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"callout warning\">\n<strong>A timeout does not prove failure.</strong> The request may have completed even when the integration did not receive the response.\n</div>","Financial Mismatches":"<p>Compare item cost, item tax, postage, postage tax, promotions, fees and total against the completed checkout and payment record.</p>\n<p>Example:</p>\n<pre class=\"structure-diagram\"><code>Customer paid for Seller item: $100\nShipping allocated at checkout: $12\nExpected Marketplacer amount: $112\nMarketplacer Invoice amount: $102\nDifference: $10</code></pre>\n<p>Investigate incorrect postage allocation, omitted discounts, tax inconsistency, first-party items included by mistake or the integration using current catalogue values instead of transaction values.</p>","Seller Did Not Receive the Order":"<p>First confirm whether the Seller Invoice exists.</p>\n<h3>Invoice exists</h3>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>confirm the correct Seller owns it</li>\n<li>inspect it in the Seller Portal</li>\n<li>review MConnect or API connection state</li>\n<li>inspect connector or Seller-system errors</li>\n<li>avoid creating a second Marketplacer Order</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Invoice does not exist</h3>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>inspect the original <code>orderCreate</code> request</li>\n<li>search using the external ID</li>\n<li>review returned errors</li>\n<li>confirm payment outcome</li>\n<li>decide whether a safe retry is possible</li>\n<li>communicate delay or cancellation to the customer</li>\n</ul>","Seller Cannot Fulfil an Item":"<p>The Seller must not mark an unavailable item as dispatched.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Confirm the exact Line Item and quantity.</li>\n<li>Determine whether the rest of the Invoice can proceed.</li>\n<li>Begin the pre-dispatch cancellation workflow.</li>\n<li>Inform the customer.</li>\n<li>Process the actual payment refund.</li>\n<li>Confirm remittance impact.</li>\n<li>investigate why unavailable stock remained purchasable.</li>\n<li>Record the cancellation in Seller performance.</li>\n</ol>","Stalled Fulfilment":"<h3>Invoice remains Paid</h3>\n<p>Check Order receipt, Seller connection, stock, dispatch SLA and whether an external dispatch failed to reach Marketplacer.</p>\n<h3>Invoice remains Paid Partially Sent</h3>\n<p>Identify whether the remainder is ready, backordered, unavailable, already shipped but unrecorded, or affected by an integration failure.</p>\n<p>Do not allow unresolved partial Invoices to remain open indefinitely.</p>","Shipment and Tracking Exceptions":"<p>Common issues include missing tracking, unrecognised Carrier names, incorrect numbers, broken URLs, missing partial Shipments or corrected details not reaching the storefront.</p>\n<p>Compare:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Marketplacer Shipment</li>\n<li>Carrier configuration</li>\n<li>tracking number and URL</li>\n<li>Seller source-system Shipment</li>\n<li>connector, API or webhook event</li>\n<li>customer-facing fulfilment state</li>\n</ol>","Integration and Webhook Failures":"<p>A Shipment may exist in Marketplacer while the storefront remains unchanged.</p>\n<p>Marketplacer treats HTTP <code>2xx</code> responses as successful webhook deliveries. Network failures, timeouts, <code>5xx</code> and <code>429</code> responses may be retried. Many other <code>4xx</code> responses are non-retriable and can lead to the webhook being disabled.</p>\n<p>When investigating:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>identify the exact event and entity</li>\n<li>review response code and body</li>\n<li>correct the endpoint before requeueing</li>\n<li>ensure replay cannot duplicate fulfilment</li>\n<li>confirm the storefront after successful processing</li>\n</ul>","Status Mismatches Between Systems":"<p>Different terminology is not necessarily an error.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>System</th>\n<th>Example status</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Marketplacer Invoice</td>\n<td>Paid Partially Sent</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Storefront</td>\n<td>Partially fulfilled</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Seller system</td>\n<td>Partially shipped</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Payment gateway</td>\n<td>Captured</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div>\n<p>Maintain a status map describing the Marketplacer state, equivalent external state, triggering event, expected timing and exception owner.</p>","Payment and Refund Exceptions":"<p>Marketplacer records Order, refund, amendment and remittance data. Actual customer funds move through the Operator's payment architecture.</p>\n<p>Investigate situations where:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>payment succeeded but no Order exists</li>\n<li>an Order exists but payment failed or reversed</li>\n<li>Marketplacer refund workflow completed but the payment refund did not</li>\n<li>customer refund differs from the Invoice Amendment</li>\n<li>Seller payout occurred before an exception was resolved</li>\n</ul>","Preserve the Evidence":"<p>Retain request and response logs, IDs, timestamps, webhook events, screenshots, communications, payment references, refund references and final resolution.</p>\n<p>Do not create replacement Orders, Shipments or refunds until existing records are identified.</p>","Escalation Levels":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Level</th>\n<th>Example</th>\n<th>Typical owner</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Operational</td>\n<td>Seller has not dispatched</td>\n<td>Operator or Seller operations</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Customer service</td>\n<td>Delay or unavailable item</td>\n<td>Customer service</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Integration</td>\n<td>Order or Shipment did not synchronise</td>\n<td>Engineering or integration partner</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Financial</td>\n<td>Payment, Invoice or remittance mismatch</td>\n<td>Finance and marketplace operations</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Platform support</td>\n<td>Platform behaviour cannot be explained</td>\n<td>Marketplacer Support</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Critical incident</td>\n<td>Widespread live-Order failure</td>\n<td>Incident response team</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div>\n<p>A Support ticket should include environment, Order and Invoice IDs, external ID, Seller, timestamps and timezone, expected and actual result, evidence, errors and business impact.</p>","Marketplace Decisions":"<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>how quickly a missing Marketplacer Order triggers an alert</li>\n<li>who approves a retry</li>\n<li>which external ID prevents duplication</li>\n<li>when Sellers are escalated for outstanding Invoices</li>\n<li>who informs the customer</li>\n<li>who completes Marketplacer and payment refund actions</li>\n<li>who monitors connector and webhook failures</li>\n<li>who owns financial reconciliation</li>\n<li>which conditions trigger a critical incident</li>\n</ul>","End-to-End Testing":"<p>Test insufficient stock, missing required fields, duplicate external ID, lost responses, Seller connection failure, partial fulfilment, unrecognised Carrier, missing tracking, webhook <code>500</code>, non-retriable <code>400</code>, corrected tracking and a refund workflow whose payment action is deliberately withheld.</p>","Operator Readiness Checklist":"<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>stable external IDs are used</li>\n<li>duplicate prevention is tested</li>\n<li>failed Order creation generates an alert</li>\n<li>request and response logs are retained</li>\n<li>payment and Order creation can be reconciled</li>\n<li>Seller stock exceptions have an escalation path</li>\n<li>Paid and Paid Partially Sent Invoices are monitored</li>\n<li>Shipment and tracking failures can be investigated</li>\n<li>connector and webhook errors are monitored</li>\n<li>customer communication templates are ready</li>\n<li>Support escalation evidence is defined</li>\n<li>repeated exceptions lead to preventive action</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/operator-api/reference/mutations/ordercreate/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">orderCreate</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/operator-api/examples/orders/howto_order/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Creating Orders</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/4409702574733-Find-orders-in-the-Seller-Portal-using-an-External-ID\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Find Orders in the Seller Portal using an External ID</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/27307693304333-Operator-welcome-screen-overview\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Operator welcome screen overview</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/webhooks/webhookretries/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Webhook Retry Policy</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360052908272-Seller-payments-and-remittance-workflow\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Seller payments and remittance workflow</a></li>\n</ul>"},"related":[["order-lifecycle","Order Lifecycle"],["fulfilment","Fulfilment and Dispatch"],["cancellation-workflow","Cancellation Workflow"],["integration-troubleshooting","Integration Troubleshooting"],["getting-support","Getting Support"]]},"additional-charges":{"summary":"Understand the separate Invoice used for governed post-order charges, the required configuration and how customer payment, tax, reporting and Seller remittance must reconcile.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Customer service","Finance","Tax and legal","Technology and integrations","Seller management"],"sections":{"What an Additional Charges Invoice Is":"<p>An Additional Charges Invoice bills the customer for an extra cost that was not part of the original Order, such as return shipping or a restocking charge.</p>\n<p>It is:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>a separate financial document</li>\n<li>linked to the original Order and Seller Invoice</li>\n<li>created from an Invoice Amendment</li>\n<li>made up of custom Line Items</li>\n<li>included in Seller reporting and payout calculations</li>\n</ul>\n<p>It does not rewrite the original Seller Invoice.</p>","Original Invoice vs Additional Charges Invoice":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Original Seller Invoice</th>\n<th>Additional Charges Invoice</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Created from the original Order</td>\n<td>Created after the Order</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Contains purchased Variants</td>\n<td>Contains custom charge Line Items</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Reflects the checkout transaction</td>\n<td>Reflects a later approved cost</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Product Line Items are tied to Variants</td>\n<td>Charges are not tied to product SKUs</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Remains the original transaction document</td>\n<td>Is a separate linked document</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div>","When to Use Additional Charges Invoices":"<p>Appropriate examples may include:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>return freight allowed by policy</li>\n<li>restocking fee allowed by policy</li>\n<li>an agreed delivery change after checkout</li>\n<li>a customer-approved specialist handling service</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Before creating the charge, confirm:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>it is permitted by customer terms and Seller agreement</li>\n<li>the customer has been informed</li>\n<li>consent evidence is retained where required</li>\n<li>amount and tax are correct</li>\n<li>the payment or refund process can reconcile it</li>\n<li>customer service can explain the charge</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"callout warning\">\n<strong>Do not surprise the customer with an unexplained fee.</strong>\n</div>","When Not to Use Them":"<p>Do not use an Additional Charges Invoice to hide or repair:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>an incorrectly configured Shipping Rule</li>\n<li>postage omitted from the original Order request</li>\n<li>an integration sending the wrong checkout value</li>\n<li>a Seller changing the product price after purchase</li>\n<li>a predictable standard fee that should have been shown at checkout</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If the customer paid the correct amount but Marketplacer received the wrong amount, investigate and reconcile the original integration issue rather than introduce another customer charge.</p>","Example: Return Shipping Charge":"<p>A customer returns a bulky item. The published return policy makes the customer responsible for a $35 return shipping fee.</p>\n<pre class=\"structure-diagram\"><code>Original Seller Invoice\nProduct: Oak side table\nOriginal amount: $240\n\nAdditional Charges Invoice\nDescription: Return Shipping Charge\nQuantity: 1\nGross amount: $35</code></pre>\n<p>The new Invoice is linked to the original transaction but does not alter the original $240 Invoice. The payment or refund process must produce the same $35 customer financial outcome recorded in Marketplacer.</p>","How Additional Charges Invoices Work":"<p>The documented Operator API workflow adds a custom Line Item to an Invoice Amendment and sets <code>issueInvoice: true</code>.</p>\n<p>This can be performed through the refund approval flow or by creating an Invoice Amendment directly, according to the approved solution.</p>\n<p>Marketplacer then creates a separate PDF Invoice, links it to the original transaction, excludes the charge from the Seller credit note and includes it in reporting and payout calculations.</p>\n<p>The current documented Seller Portal workflow focuses on viewing and downloading the resulting Invoice. Creation should be restricted to the authorised Operator-side process.</p>","One Invoice per Amendment":"<p>One amendment containing several invoiced custom charges creates one Additional Charges Invoice for that amendment.</p>\n<pre class=\"structure-diagram\"><code>Amendment\n├── Return freight: $25\n└── Restocking fee: $10\n\nResult: one Additional Charges Invoice for $35</code></pre>\n<p>A later amendment creates a separate Additional Charges Invoice.</p>","Custom Line Items":"<p>Use clear approved descriptions such as:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>Return Shipping Charge</li>\n<li>Restocking Fee</li>\n<li>Additional Delivery Service</li>\n<li>Remote Access Delivery Surcharge</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Avoid vague wording such as Fee, Adjustment or Other.</p>\n<p>Custom charge Line Items are not tied to a product SKU or Variant.</p>","Configuration Requirements":"<p>Two settings are required:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Configuration → Seller Settings → Enable advanced amendments</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Configuration → Finance Settings → Enable additional charges invoice</strong></li>\n</ol>\n<p>Review Advanced Amendments with the Marketplacer Delivery and technical teams before activation, particularly because it changes the amendment workflow used by the marketplace.</p>","Invoice Branding and Display":"<p>Invoice-visibility settings can also affect Additional Charges Invoices, including:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>Hide Seller information on Invoices</li>\n<li>Hide Operator information on Invoices</li>\n<li>Allow Sellers to add custom footer text</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Download a sample document in Sandbox and verify legal entity, customer details, Seller details, tax, branding, description and transaction reference.</p>","Where Operators Find the Invoice":"<p>In the Operator Portal:</p>\n<p><strong>Orders → All Sales</strong></p>\n<p>Locate the original transaction and use the <strong>Additional Charges Invoice</strong> column to download the document.</p>\n<p>Retain the relationship between the original Order, Seller Invoice, Refund Request where applicable, Invoice Amendment, Additional Charges Invoice, customer payment reference and remittance record.</p>","Where Sellers Find the Invoice":"<p>Sellers can download the document from Seller Portal 2.0 through:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li><strong>Orders → All Refund Requests</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Orders → All Orders</strong></li>\n<li>the Invoice detail view</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The available menu option is <strong>View Additional Charges Invoice(s)</strong>.</p>","Customer Payment and Refund Reconciliation":"<p>Creating the Marketplacer document does not, by itself, prove that the customer's payment method has been charged.</p>\n<p>The amount may be collected separately or reflected in the final refund, depending on the marketplace's payment design.</p>\n<p>Reconcile:</p>\n<pre class=\"structure-diagram\"><code>Customer financial outcome\n            ↕\nPayment or refund provider\n            ↕\nStorefront transaction\n            ↕\nMarketplacer Invoice Amendment\n            ↕\nAdditional Charges Invoice\n            ↕\nSeller remittance and payout</code></pre>","Tax and Credit Notes":"<p>The separate Invoice supports tax compliance where the original tax Invoice cannot be modified.</p>\n<p>Marketplacer creates a separate document, includes relevant tax details and excludes the invoiced charge from the Seller credit note to avoid duplicate treatment.</p>\n<p>The Operator remains responsible for correct tax rate, issuing entity, wording, accounting treatment and local requirements.</p>","Seller Remittance":"<p>Current Marketplacer documentation states that the full value of the additional charge is included in the Seller payout and treated like another custom Line Item.</p>\n<p>Confirm how this interacts with tax withholding, payout timing, commission policy, the payment provider and the Seller agreement.</p>","Reporting":"<p>Finance teams should be able to identify:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>original sale</li>\n<li>reason for the charge</li>\n<li>Additional Charges Invoice</li>\n<li>payment or refund treatment</li>\n<li>amount remitted to the Seller</li>\n<li>tax recorded</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Additional charges appear in Seller and refund reporting linked to the original transaction.</p>","Marketplace Policy Decisions":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Decision</th>\n<th>Question</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Permitted charges</td>\n<td>Which post-order costs may be passed to customers?</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Customer consent</td>\n<td>What approval evidence is required?</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Authority</td>\n<td>Which Operator role may create or approve a charge?</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Seller request</td>\n<td>How does a Seller request the charge?</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Tax</td>\n<td>Which rate and legal entity apply?</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Payment</td>\n<td>How will the customer actually pay?</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Refund interaction</td>\n<td>Is the charge deducted from a refund or collected separately?</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Seller payout</td>\n<td>How and when is the charge remitted?</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Dispute</td>\n<td>What happens if the customer rejects the charge?</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div>","Operational Approval Process":"<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>Valid charge identified</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>Policy confirmed</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><div><strong>Customer informed and consent recorded</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><div><strong>Finance confirms amount and tax</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><div><strong>Authorised amendment created</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">6</span><div><strong>Additional Charges Invoice generated</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">7</span><div><strong>Payment or refund process completed</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">8</span><div><strong>Seller payout and reporting reconciled</strong></div></div></div>","Common Risks":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Risk</th>\n<th>Preventive control</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Customer was not informed</td>\n<td>Require recorded approval</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Charge belonged at checkout</td>\n<td>Review shipping or integration configuration</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Incorrect tax</td>\n<td>Finance review and Sandbox test</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Charge created twice</td>\n<td>Use amendment and payment references</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Invoice exists but no payment action occurred</td>\n<td>Reconcile payment or refund process</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Customer charged but Invoice not created</td>\n<td>Monitor API and amendment failures</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Vague description</td>\n<td>Use approved standard descriptions</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div>","End-to-End Testing":"<p>Test settings, API creation, several charges in one amendment, one Invoice per amendment, PDF appearance, original Invoice preservation, credit-note exclusion, Operator and Seller downloads, tax totals, reporting, payout calculation, customer payment or refund reconciliation and duplicate prevention.</p>","Operator Readiness Checklist":"<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>policy and permitted charge types are documented</li>\n<li>Advanced Amendments and Finance settings are approved</li>\n<li>authorised creation method is defined</li>\n<li>customer consent requirements are documented</li>\n<li>standard descriptions are available</li>\n<li>tax treatment is approved</li>\n<li>payment or refund process is integrated</li>\n<li>Operator and Seller can find the document</li>\n<li>Finance can reconcile the charge</li>\n<li>Seller payout treatment is understood</li>\n<li>dispute and reversal processes are documented</li>\n<li>end-to-end Sandbox testing is complete</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/37709603707405-Additional-charges-invoices-overview\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Additional charges invoices overview</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/37709580190733-Manage-additional-charges-invoices-as-a-seller\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Manage additional charges invoices as a Seller</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/operator-api/examples/refunds/howto_additional_charges/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Additional Charges</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/25930591592973-Seller-settings\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Seller Settings</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/31441597254285-Finance-Settings\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Finance Settings</a></li>\n</ul>"},"related":[["order-exceptions","Order Exceptions"],["refund-financial-adjustments","Refund Financial Adjustments"],["finance-reporting","Invoice Configuration"],["tax","Tax Model and Hierarchy"],["finance-reporting","Financial Reconciliation"]]},"test-orders":{"summary":"Validate the Shipping, Order and fulfilment design with controlled test Orders before the broader marketplace-wide Testing and Go-Live programme.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Testing and delivery teams","Sellers","Customer service","Finance","Ecommerce and technology"],"sections":{"Test Scope":"<p>This page tests the Order and fulfilment workflow covered in Sprint 8. It does not replace the complete marketplace UAT, Production readiness, launch sign-off or hypercare process in <strong>Testing and Go-Live</strong>.</p>\n<p>The Sprint 8 test should prove that:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>shipping is calculated and recorded correctly</li>\n<li>one-Seller and multi-Seller Orders create correctly</li>\n<li>Seller Invoices contain the correct Line Items</li>\n<li>Sellers receive and dispatch the Invoice through the intended system</li>\n<li>complete and partial Shipments return to the storefront</li>\n<li>Carrier and tracking information are usable</li>\n<li>unavailable quantities follow the correct exception path</li>\n<li>Order, Invoice, Shipment and financial values reconcile</li>\n</ul>","Prepare the Test Order":"<p>Use representative Sandbox data:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>at least one active test Seller</li>\n<li>approved products and Variants</li>\n<li>correct stock</li>\n<li>assigned Shipping Profiles where used</li>\n<li>one simple product</li>\n<li>one multi-quantity or multi-Variant product</li>\n<li>two Sellers for a multi-Seller scenario</li>\n<li>a controlled test customer</li>\n<li>non-production payment and integration configuration</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Create a shared test record containing environment, scenario ID, storefront Order ID, Marketplacer Order and Invoice IDs, Seller source-system ID, Shipment ID, tracking number, expected result, actual result, evidence and owner.</p>","Test Shipping at Checkout":"<p>When Marketplacer Shipping Rules are used:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Confirm the Variant Profile.</li>\n<li>Enter a postcode in the intended Zone.</li>\n<li>Confirm the expected Rate is returned.</li>\n<li>Verify the storefront displays it.</li>\n<li>Complete checkout.</li>\n<li>Confirm the same postage amount is submitted with <code>orderCreate</code>.</li>\n<li>Confirm the Seller Invoice records the amount.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>When shipping is calculated outside Marketplacer, confirm the external amount displayed to the customer is the same amount submitted to Marketplacer.</p>\n<p>Test a standard postcode, remote postcode, unsupported postcode, quantity change, multi-Seller cart and free-shipping or bulky scenario where applicable.</p>","Test Order Creation and Invoice Splitting":"<p>Confirm:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>exactly one Marketplacer Order is created</li>\n<li>the external storefront reference is stored</li>\n<li>customer and address data are correct</li>\n<li>only intended Seller items are included</li>\n<li>Variant IDs and quantities are correct</li>\n<li>item, postage, tax and promotion values match checkout</li>\n<li>one Invoice is created for each participating Seller</li>\n<li>each Invoice contains only that Seller's Line Items</li>\n<li>first-party items remain in the intended Operator system</li>\n<li>no duplicate Order exists</li>\n</ul>","Test Seller Order Receipt":"<h3>Connected Seller</h3>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>Invoice appears in the Seller source system</li>\n<li>correct items and quantities are present</li>\n<li>external references are retained</li>\n<li>no duplicate source-system Order is created</li>\n<li>Seller knows to dispatch from the connected platform</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Seller Portal user</h3>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>Seller can locate the Invoice</li>\n<li>customer and delivery details are visible as intended</li>\n<li>packing slip and approved Carrier options are available</li>\n<li>the Seller understands the dispatch SLA</li>\n<li>external ID search works where configured</li>\n</ul>","Test Complete Dispatch":"<p>Have the Seller dispatch every Line Item and quantity.</p>\n<p>Confirm:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>correct quantities are dispatched</li>\n<li>Carrier and tracking are accepted</li>\n<li>one Shipment is created</li>\n<li>Seller Portal shows <strong>Paid Sent</strong></li>\n<li>API status flags include <code>PAID</code> and <code>SENT</code></li>\n<li>Shipment reaches the storefront</li>\n<li>customer sees the correct tracking information</li>\n<li>the tracking link opens correctly</li>\n</ul>","Test Partial Dispatch and Multiple Shipments":"<p>Create an Invoice with several Line Items or a quantity greater than one.</p>\n<p>Dispatch only part, then dispatch the remainder later.</p>\n<p>Confirm:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>first Shipment contains only selected quantities</li>\n<li>Invoice becomes <strong>Paid Partially Sent</strong></li>\n<li>remaining quantities stay outstanding</li>\n<li>storefront shows partial fulfilment</li>\n<li>a second Shipment can be created</li>\n<li>each Shipment has the correct Carrier and tracking number</li>\n<li>Invoice becomes <strong>Paid Sent</strong> only after every quantity is resolved</li>\n</ul>","Test Tracking and Carrier Handling":"<p>Test:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>valid Carrier and tracking number</li>\n<li>alternative Carrier name</li>\n<li>unrecognised Carrier</li>\n<li>missing tracking where permitted</li>\n<li>incorrect tracking URL</li>\n<li>correction after dispatch</li>\n<li>several tracking numbers on one Invoice</li>\n<li>different Carriers across Shipments</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Confirm which issues are visible to the Operator and customer service teams and whether post-dispatch corrections reach the storefront.</p>","Test an Unavailable Item":"<p>Create a scenario where one Line Item or quantity cannot be fulfilled.</p>\n<p>Confirm:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>available quantities can still be dispatched where appropriate</li>\n<li>unavailable quantity is not falsely shipped</li>\n<li>the correct cancellation workflow begins</li>\n<li>customer communication is triggered</li>\n<li>storefront and Marketplacer reach the same final state</li>\n<li>refund and remittance consequences can be reconciled</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The detailed cancellation and refund workflow is tested in <strong>Cancellations, Returns and Refunds</strong>. The complete marketplace launch journey is tested again in <strong>Testing and Go-Live</strong>.</p>","Reconcile the Order Across Systems":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>System</th>\n<th>What should agree</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Storefront</td>\n<td>Customer Order, items, shipping and fulfilment</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Payment provider</td>\n<td>Amount authorised or captured</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Marketplacer Order</td>\n<td>Customer and marketplace transaction</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Seller Invoice</td>\n<td>Seller-specific items and values</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Seller source system</td>\n<td>Order and fulfilment record</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Shipments</td>\n<td>Quantities, Carrier and tracking</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Remittance data</td>\n<td>Seller payable amount and fulfilment consequences</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div>\n<p>Use transaction values stored on the Order and Invoice, not current product values.</p>","Record Test Evidence":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Field</th>\n<th>Evidence</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Scenario</td>\n<td>Single Seller, multi-Seller, partial dispatch or exception</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Environment</td>\n<td>Sandbox</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Storefront Order ID</td>\n<td>External reference</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Marketplacer Order and Invoice IDs</td>\n<td>Platform references</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Seller</td>\n<td>Test Seller</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Expected result</td>\n<td>Approved outcome</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Actual result</td>\n<td>Observed outcome</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Screenshots or payloads</td>\n<td>Evidence from each system</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Defect or decision</td>\n<td>Owner and resolution</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Retest result</td>\n<td>Passed, failed or blocked</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div>","Exit Criteria":"<p>The Order and fulfilment flow is ready to progress when:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>shipping values reconcile</li>\n<li>single-Seller and multi-Seller splitting pass</li>\n<li>each Seller receives the correct Invoice</li>\n<li>complete and partial dispatch pass</li>\n<li>tracking reaches the customer experience</li>\n<li>unavailable quantities follow the approved exception route</li>\n<li>external IDs support investigation</li>\n<li>no unresolved critical Order or fulfilment defect remains</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Broader configuration validation, formal launch blockers, Production smoke tests, launch sign-off and hypercare remain in <strong>Testing and Go-Live</strong>.</p>","Operator Readiness Checklist":"<ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li>representative Seller and product data are available</li>\n<li>shipping source and test scenarios are documented</li>\n<li>one-Seller and multi-Seller Orders pass</li>\n<li>first-party and Seller items are separated correctly</li>\n<li>financial values reconcile with checkout</li>\n<li>complete and partial dispatch pass</li>\n<li>multiple Shipments display correctly</li>\n<li>Carrier and tracking behaviour is verified</li>\n<li>unavailable-stock handling is tested</li>\n<li>every system reference is recorded</li>\n<li>defects have owners and retest evidence</li>\n<li>Order and fulfilment exit criteria are approved</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\">\n<li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/operator-api/examples/orders/howto_order/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Creating Orders</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/operator-api/reference/mutations/ordercreate/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">orderCreate</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/8838299197197-Dispatch-orders-from-the-Seller-Portal\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Dispatch orders from the Seller Portal</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/seller-api/examples/shipping/creating_shipments/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Creating Shipments</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/4409702574733-Find-orders-in-the-Seller-Portal-using-an-External-ID\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Find Orders in the Seller Portal using an External ID</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360052908272-Seller-payments-and-remittance-workflow\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Seller payments and remittance workflow</a></li>\n</ul>"},"related":[["testing-strategy","Testing Strategy"],["end-to-end-testing","End-to-End Testing"],["seller-launch-readiness","Seller Launch Readiness"],["order-exceptions","Order Exceptions"],["production-readiness","Production Readiness"]]}};
